<br>
I'm gettin' kinda tired of all the people who are whining about warnings. I like the system we have. I like the board like it is.<br>
<br>
The system as I see it:<br>
<br>
The mods warn when they see fit, and when they are in the mood.<br>
<br>
You scream bloody murder.<br>
<br>
Here is the analogy:<br>
<br>
In America (look I realize not everyone is in america!!) we have something called Speed Limits. I personally see them as somewhat of a suggestion than a rule, and the only reason I obey them is not for my safety but rather out of fear of getting a ticket. I break the law every day, but only a little bit and not majorly like I would sometimes like becuase I fear the points that come along with the ticket. <br>
<br>
Sometimes I pass cops while going 80 and they sit there. Once or twice I've passed them going 74 and I've gotten pulled. Its the game you play. You weigh the benefits against the risks constantly, and unconciously.<br>
<br>
The mods on here are totally the police. The law is the rules. Are they going to pull over every single speeder they see? No. If they did that they would not have the time to eat, drink, sleep, go to the bathroom, watch American Idol, or fight other crimes. So rather they pull over the REALLY bad ones, and they pull over a few here and there to keep people on their toes. And some of those they let go. <br>
<br>
So see warnings like you see speeding tickets. You walk a fine line if you choose to flame someone, and realize at any point there might be a mod around the corner with a radar gun in hand. You might get warned, you might not. If you do... don't bitch about it.<br>
<br>
And for God's sake don't pull over and yell at a cop who is giving someone else a ticket because you sped three days ago.<br>
<br>
Kuladen<br>
